15 (b) An appeal under subsection (4)(a) must be submitted in writing within 15 business days of the
16 challenged decision, stating the facts and raising all grounds for appeal that the party may raise in district court.
17 (c) The governing body shall hear the appeal de novo. The governing body is not bound by the
18 decision that has been appealed, but the appeal must be limited to the issues raised on appeal. The appellant
19 has the burden of proving that the appealed decision was made in error.
